#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn47.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Ambapālivagga "
msgstr "1. In Ambapālī’s Wood "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 10. Bhikkhunupassayasutta → bhikkhunivāsako (pts1)
msgctxt "sn47.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Bhikkhunupassayasutta "
msgstr "10. The Nuns’ Quarters "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn47.10:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena aññataro bhikkhunupassayo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the nuns’ quarters, and sat down on the seat spread out. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhuniyo yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho tā bhikkhuniyo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then several nuns went up to Venerable Ānanda bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.155, sc2
#. VAR: suppatiṭṭhitacittā → supaṭṭhitacittā (bj, mr) | supatiṭṭhitacittā (s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: sañjānantī”ti → sampajānantīti (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn47.10:2.1"
msgid "“Idha, bhante ānanda, sambahulā bhikkhuniyo catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacittā viharantiyo uḷāraṃ pubbenāparaṃ visesaṃ sañjānantī”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, Ānanda, several nuns meditate with their minds firmly established in the four kinds of mindfulness meditation. They have realized a higher distinction than they had before.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.10:2.2"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, bhaginiyo, evametaṃ, bhaginiyo. "
msgstr "“That’s how it is, sisters! That’s how it is, sisters! "

msgctxt "sn47.10:2.3"
msgid "Yo hi koci, bhaginiyo, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacitto viharati, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ: "
msgstr "Any monk or nun who meditates with their mind firmly established in the four kinds of mindfulness meditation can expect to "

# NOTE: See my note on AN 7.49. I don’t see how BB can reconcile his translation (based on the commentary) with the fact that visesa here is singular.
msgctxt "sn47.10:2.4"
msgid "‘uḷāraṃ pubbenāparaṃ visesaṃ sañjānissatī’”ti. "
msgstr "realize a higher distinction than they had before.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn47.10:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando tā bhikkhuniyo dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi. "
msgstr "Then Ānanda educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired those nuns with a Dhamma talk, after which he got up from his seat and left. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:3.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Ānanda wandered for alms in Sāvatthī. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn47.10:4.1"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena aññataro bhikkhunupassayo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdiṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn47.10:4.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, sambahulā bhikkhuniyo yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho, bhante, tā bhikkhuniyo maṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn47.10:4.3"
msgid "‘idha, bhante ānanda, sambahulā bhikkhuniyo catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacittā viharantiyo uḷāraṃ pubbenāparaṃ visesaṃ sañjānantī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn47.10:4.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vuttāhaṃ, bhante, tā bhikkhuniyo etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn47.10:4.5"
msgid "‘evametaṃ, bhaginiyo, evametaṃ, bhaginiyo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn47.10:4.6"
msgid "Yo hi koci, bhaginiyo, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacitto viharati, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—uḷāraṃ pubbenāparaṃ visesaṃ sañjānissatī’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn47.10:5.1"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, ānanda, evametaṃ, ānanda. "
msgstr "“That’s so true, Ānanda! That’s so true! "

msgctxt "sn47.10:5.2"
msgid "Yo hi koci, ānanda, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacitto viharati, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ: "
msgstr "Any monk or nun who meditates with their mind firmly established in the four kinds of mindfulness meditation can expect to "

#. VAR: sañjānissati → sañjānissatīti (bahūsu)
msgctxt "sn47.10:5.3"
msgid "‘uḷāraṃ pubbenāparaṃ visesaṃ sañjānissati’. "
msgstr "realize a higher distinction than they had before. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.156, sc6
msgctxt "sn47.10:6.1"
msgid "Katamesu catūsu? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn47.10:6.2"
msgid "Idhānanda, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

# NOTE: It’s difficult to get around “fever” here for parilaha, obviously it’s not talking about illness.
msgctxt "sn47.10:6.3"
msgid "Tassa kāye kāyānupassino viharato kāyārammaṇo vā uppajjati kāyasmiṃ pariḷāho, cetaso vā līnattaṃ, bahiddhā vā cittaṃ vikkhipati. "
msgstr "As they meditate observing an aspect of the body, based on the body there arises physical tension, or mental sluggishness, or the mind is externally scattered. "

#. VAR: Tenānanda → tena hānanda (bj) | tena ānanda (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn47.10:6.4"
msgid "Tenānanda, bhikkhunā kismiñcideva pasādanīye nimitte cittaṃ paṇidahitabbaṃ. "
msgstr "That mendicant should direct their mind towards an inspiring foundation. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:6.5"
msgid "Tassa kismiñcideva pasādanīye nimitte cittaṃ paṇidahato pāmojjaṃ jāyati. "
msgstr "As they do so, joy springs up. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:6.6"
msgid "Pamuditassa pīti jāyati. "
msgstr "Being joyful, rapture springs up. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:6.7"
msgid "Pītimanassa kāyo passambhati. "
msgstr "When the mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. "

#. VAR: vedayati → vediyati (bj)
msgctxt "sn47.10:6.8"
msgid "Passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedayati. "
msgstr "When the body is tranquil, one feels bliss. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:6.9"
msgid "Sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati. "
msgstr "And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed in samādhi. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:6.10"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "Then they reflect: "

msgctxt "sn47.10:6.11"
msgid "‘yassa khvāhaṃ atthāya cittaṃ paṇidahiṃ, so me attho abhinipphanno. "
msgstr "‘I have accomplished the goal for which I directed my mind. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:6.12"
msgid "Handa dāni paṭisaṃharāmī’ti. "
msgstr "Let me now pull back.’ "

msgctxt "sn47.10:6.13"
msgid "So paṭisaṃharati ceva na ca vitakketi na ca vicāreti. "
msgstr "They pull back, and neither place the mind nor keep it connected. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:6.14"
msgid "‘Avitakkomhi avicāro, ajjhattaṃ satimā sukhamasmī’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘I’m neither placing the mind nor keeping it connected. Mindful within myself, I’m happy.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn47.10:7.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhu vedanāsu … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "sn47.10:7.2"
msgid "citte … pe … "
msgstr "mind … "

msgctxt "sn47.10:7.3"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:7.4"
msgid "Tassa dhammesu dhammānupassino viharato dhammārammaṇo vā uppajjati kāyasmiṃ pariḷāho, cetaso vā līnattaṃ, bahiddhā vā cittaṃ vikkhipati. "
msgstr "As they meditate observing an aspect of principles, based on principles there arises physical tension, or mental sluggishness, or the mind is externally scattered. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:7.5"
msgid "Tenānanda, bhikkhunā kismiñcideva pasādanīye nimitte cittaṃ paṇidahitabbaṃ. "
msgstr "That mendicant should direct their mind towards an inspiring foundation. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:7.6"
msgid "Tassa kismiñcideva pasādanīye nimitte cittaṃ paṇidahato pāmojjaṃ jāyati. "
msgstr "As they do so, joy springs up. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:7.7"
msgid "Pamuditassa pīti jāyati. "
msgstr "Being joyful, rapture springs up. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:7.8"
msgid "Pītimanassa kāyo passambhati. "
msgstr "When the mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:7.9"
msgid "Passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedayati. "
msgstr "When the body is tranquil, one feels bliss. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:7.10"
msgid "Sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati. "
msgstr "And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed in samādhi. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:7.11"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "Then they reflect: "

msgctxt "sn47.10:7.12"
msgid "‘yassa khvāhaṃ atthāya cittaṃ paṇidahiṃ, so me attho abhinipphanno. "
msgstr "‘I have accomplished the goal for which I directed my mind. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:7.13"
msgid "Handa dāni paṭisaṃharāmī’ti. "
msgstr "Let me now pull back.’ "

msgctxt "sn47.10:7.14"
msgid "So paṭisaṃharati ceva na ca vitakketi na ca vicāreti. "
msgstr "They pull back, and neither place the mind nor keep it connected. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:7.15"
msgid "‘Avitakkomhi avicāro, ajjhattaṃ satimā sukhamasmī’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘I’m neither placing the mind nor keeping it connected. Mindful within myself, I’m happy.’ "

msgctxt "sn47.10:7.16"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, ānanda, paṇidhāya bhāvanā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how there is directed development. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.157, sc8
msgctxt "sn47.10:8.1"
msgid "Kathañcānanda, appaṇidhāya bhāvanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is there undirected development? "

msgctxt "sn47.10:8.2"
msgid "Bahiddhā, ānanda, bhikkhu cittaṃ appaṇidhāya ‘appaṇihitaṃ me bahiddhā cittan’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "Not directing their mind externally, a mendicant understands: ‘My mind is not directed externally.’ "

# NOTE: See note on AN 7.61 for pacchapure.
msgctxt "sn47.10:8.3"
msgid "Atha pacchāpure ‘asaṅkhittaṃ vimuttaṃ appaṇihitan’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "And they understand: ‘Over a period of time it’s unconstricted, freed, and undirected.’ "

msgctxt "sn47.10:8.4"
msgid "Atha ca pana ‘kāye kāyānupassī viharāmi ātāpī sampajāno satimā sukhamasmī’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "And they also understand: ‘I meditate observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, mindful; I am happy.’ "

msgctxt "sn47.10:8.5"
msgid "Bahiddhā, ānanda, bhikkhu cittaṃ appaṇidhāya ‘appaṇihitaṃ me bahiddhā cittan’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "Not directing their mind externally, a mendicant understands: ‘My mind is not directed externally.’ "

msgctxt "sn47.10:8.6"
msgid "Atha pacchāpure ‘asaṅkhittaṃ vimuttaṃ appaṇihitan’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "And they understand: ‘Over a period of time it’s unconstricted, freed, and undirected.’ "

msgctxt "sn47.10:8.7"
msgid "Atha ca pana ‘vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharāmi ātāpī sampajāno satimā sukhamasmī’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "And they also understand: ‘I meditate observing an aspect of feelings—keen, aware, mindful; I am happy.’ "

msgctxt "sn47.10:8.8"
msgid "Bahiddhā, ānanda, bhikkhu cittaṃ appaṇidhāya ‘appaṇihitaṃ me bahiddhā cittan’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "Not directing their mind externally, a mendicant understands: ‘My mind is not directed externally.’ "

msgctxt "sn47.10:8.9"
msgid "Atha pacchāpure ‘asaṅkhittaṃ vimuttaṃ appaṇihitan’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "And they understand: ‘Over a period of time it’s unconstricted, freed, and undirected.’ "

msgctxt "sn47.10:8.10"
msgid "Atha ca pana ‘citte cittānupassī viharāmi ātāpī sampajāno satimā sukhamasmī’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "And they also understand: ‘I meditate observing an aspect of the mind—keen, aware, mindful; I am happy.’ "

msgctxt "sn47.10:8.11"
msgid "Bahiddhā, ānanda, bhikkhu cittaṃ appaṇidhāya ‘appaṇihitaṃ me bahiddhā cittan’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "Not directing their mind externally, a mendicant understands: ‘My mind is not directed externally.’ "

msgctxt "sn47.10:8.12"
msgid "Atha pacchāpure ‘asaṅkhittaṃ vimuttaṃ appaṇihitan’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "And they understand: ‘Over a period of time it’s unconstricted, freed, and undirected.’ "

msgctxt "sn47.10:8.13"
msgid "Atha ca pana ‘dhammesu dhammānupassī viharāmi ātāpī sampajāno satimā sukhamasmī’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "And they also understand: ‘I meditate observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, mindful; I am happy.’ "

msgctxt "sn47.10:8.14"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, ānanda, appaṇidhāya bhāvanā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how there is undirected development. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn47.10:9.1"
msgid "Iti kho, ānanda, desitā mayā paṇidhāya bhāvanā, desitā appaṇidhāya bhāvanā. "
msgstr "So, Ānanda, I’ve taught you directed development and undirected development. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:9.2"
msgid "Yaṃ, ānanda, satthārā karaṇīyaṃ sāvakānaṃ hitesinā anukampakena anukampaṃ upādāya, kataṃ vo taṃ mayā. "
msgstr "Out of compassion, I’ve done what a teacher should do who wants what’s best for their disciples. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:9.3"
msgid "Etāni, ānanda, rukkhamūlāni, etāni suññāgārāni. Jhāyathānanda, mā pamādattha; mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha. Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī”ti. "
msgstr "Here are these roots of trees, and here are these empty huts. Practice absorption, mendicants! Don’t be negligent! Don’t regret it later! This is my instruction to you.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn47.10:10.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "sn47.10:10.2"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.10:10.3"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.10:10.4"
msgid "Ambapālivaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.158, sc11
msgctxt "sn47.10:11.1"
msgid "Ambapāli sato bhikkhu, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.10:11.2"
msgid "Sālā kusalarāsi ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.10:11.3"
msgid "Sakuṇagghi makkaṭo sūdo, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.10:11.4"
msgid "Gilāno bhikkhunupassayoti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
